                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d853">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/521: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-01T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 1, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Department’s no. 635, December 5. Turkish Embassy is again pressing the
                    question of possible acquisition of ships by Turkey. The Department believes it
                    desirable for you to discuss the matter with the Turkish authorities along the
                    lines of the Department’s telegram under reference, and will be glad to learn
                    the Turkish Government’s reaction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
